
                                            The council has warned that this move will deepen the Israeli-Palastinian conflict and cause upheaval.

                                         JOHANNESBURG - The South African Council of Churches has described US president Donald Trump's decision to recognize Jerusalem as Israel's capital a monumental geopolitical move that could trigger lasting repercussions. This week, Trump announced his administration would begin the process of moving the US embassy in Tel Aviv to Jerusalem The council has warned that this move will deepen the Israeli-Palastinian conflict and cause upheaval and instability in the already volatile middle east region. It also says the declaration by trump means the US must forfeit its role as a peace broker between the nations. The council' reverend Malusi Mpumulwana said, “We believe Jerusalem should be resolved as part of the resolution of the two states solution.”